  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "1 Adult Serving = 2 Kids Servings\nBring a large pan of salted water to the boil and cook the orzo following pack instructions."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "While the orzo's cooking, toast the pine nuts in a dry frying pan over a medium heat until golden, then remove from the heat."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Peel the garlic and grate the Parmesan. Zest and juice the lemon."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Into a blender, add the mint, basil and toasted pine nuts (saving a few nuts and leaves for topping), garlic, lemon zest and most of the lemon juice, plus a ladle of pasta water, spinach, most of the Parmesan, a good glug of olive oil, and a pinch of salt and pepper. Blitz until smooth, that’s your pesto done."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Drain the orzo and mix with your spinach pesto."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Serve up!\nKids Plate: Dish up the kids, add a little extra cheese if they'd like.\nParents Plate: Dish out the orzo, squeezing over a touch more lemon juice for extra zing along with the remaining toasted pine nuts, basil leaves and grated parmesan to garnish. Finish with a crack of black pepper."
    }
